            <td><a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-img-tag/">&lt;img&gt;</a></td>
            <td>Embed an image</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-ul-tag/">&lt;ul&gt;</a></td>
            <td>Defines an unordered list</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-ol-tag/">&lt;ol&gt;</a></td>
            <td>Defines an ordered list</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-li-tag/">&lt;li&gt;</a></td>
            <td>Defines a list item</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-tables/">&lt;table&gt;</a></td>
            <td>Defines a table</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-forms/">&lt;form&gt;</a></td>
            <td>Defines an HTML form</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</center>
    <h1>HTML atributes</h1>
    <h3><p>
       Attributes provide additional information about an element. They are placed inside the opening tag and are written as name="value". Common attributes include class, id,<a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-href-attribute/"> href</a>, and <a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-src-attribute/">src</a>. 
    </p></h3>
    <h2>Example</h2>
    <h3><img src="/Screenshot_16-7-2025_131526_www.geeksforgeeks.org.jpeg"></h3>
    <ul><li>href is an attribute of the &it; a &gt; tag that defines the URL of the link.</li></ul>
    <h2>Web Browser</h2>
    <p>Unlike other programming languages, HTML does not show output on the any compiler.<a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/blogs/web-browser-a-complete-overview/">Web browsers</a> is an compiler which show the results of an your HTML code.

      It reads HTML files and determines how to show content with the help of HTML tags. Any web browser (Google, <a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/techtips/apple-safari-browser/">Safari</a>, <a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/techtips/mozilla-firefox-browser/">Mozilla Firefox</a> , etc) can be used to open a . HTML file and view the results.</p>
